      <p>This section is the retention magazine view of home goods stores: not which app has the prettiest templates, but which inbox moments actually move repeat purchase when larger catalogs, style preferences, and delayed purchase cycles dominate operations.</p>
      <p>Start with consent archaeology. Map every popup, checkout, footer, SMS keyword, and partner import that feeds email. home goods stores often fail when giveaway subscribers receive the same welcome as high-intent product-page signups.</p>
      <p>Week-one deliverable: welcome segmented by source with suppressions for existing customers, recent purchasers, and employees. If your current tool cannot branch on signup source, that is the selection constraint — not missing AI copy features.</p>
